Carta Johannis Smalwod burgenfis de Renfrw.

BE yt knawyn tyl al and syndry thrw thir present letterys, me Jon of Smalwod burges of Renfrw, tyl be fullely asythyt and payt of thre pwndis achte to me, thrw the Abbot and the convent of Passay, for the landis beand in the burch of Renfrw callit Beltonland, betwex the landis of Thom Makyson of the west parte of the ta parte, and the landis os Jon WVatson of the est parte of a nothir parte 3 of the qulk Ioum of thre pwndis, I the said John, my ayris, exsequituris and effygnyS, the said Abbot and con- vent of Passay frely qutchmya alsweyl nowbeand as fortocum for ayle- stand. In wytnesynge of the qulk thyngis, in defalte I haif na seyl of myn awyn, I haif procuryt wyth instans the seylis of worschipful men.
